Description: Body sherd of Milesian Fikellura pottery oinochoe; white slip; exterior: part of painted lotus flower and bud (pendant) with narrow brown band above.
Curator's comments: For parallels, see Schaus, G. 'Two Fikellura Vase Painters', Annual of the British School at Athens 81, 1986, 267, fig. 5, no. 15. Sherd possibly belongs to the same vessel as British Museum 1888,0601.561q.
Bibliographic references: Johnston 1978 / Pottery from Naukratis: An Exhibition on the Occasion of the 11th International Congress of Classical Archaeology (no. 60)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GF.132)
